**ReactOS** (more readable than Wine for AFD internals)
- https://github.com/reactos/reactos/blob/master/drivers/network/afd/include/afd.h — full AFD struct definitions
- https://github.com/reactos/reactos/blob/master/drivers/network/afd/afd/info.c — handles `IOCTL_AFD_SET_INFO` specifically


**libuv**
- https://github.com/libuv/libuv/blob/v1.x/src/win/winapi.h — AFD struct definitions (`AFD_INFO`, poll structs, IOCTL codes)
- https://github.com/libuv/libuv/blob/v1.x/src/win/winsock.c — where `NtDeviceIoControlFile` is called into AFD
- https://github.com/libuv/libuv/blob/v1.x/src/win/poll.c — AFD poll IOCTL usage for event notification

**Wine**
- https://gitlab.winehq.org/wine/wine/-/blob/master/include/wine/afd.h — Wine's AFD header, has `AFD_INFO` and IOCTL definitions
- https://gitlab.winehq.org/wine/wine/-/blob/master/dlls/ws2_32/socket.c — Winsock implementation that calls into AFD
- https://gitlab.winehq.org/wine/wine/-/blob/master/dlls/ntdll/unix/socket.c — lower-level socket/AFD handling in ntdll

Worth noting that libuv's AFD usage was significantly expanded around v1.40 when they moved to using AFD poll directly for better IOCTL performance on Windows — the git blame and changelog around that version is worth reading if you want to understand the motivation.
